{{Centurybox|-37}}
The '''37th century BC''' was a [[century]] which lasted from the year 3700 BC to 3601 BC.

==Events==
* In the [[south of England]], a rapid expansion of monument building occurred around 3700 BC.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2011/jun/06/archaeology-dating-property-boom-3700bc |title=Archaeology dating technique uncovers 'property boom' of 3700 BC |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=June 6, 2011 |accessdate=July 18, 2011}}</ref>
* In the city of [[Uruk]], southern [[Mesopotamia]], groups of tokens representing commercial transactions begin to be enclosed in hollow clay balls and kept in archives.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-978283.html# |title=From lumps of clay to arithmetic and grammar |first= |last= |work=[[The Washington Post]] |publisher=[[Highbeam Research]] |year=December 6, 1993 |accessdate=September 2, 2012}} {{subscription required}}</ref>
* The [[Maykop culture]], a major Bronze Age archaeological culture in the Western Caucasus region of Southern Russia, began around 3700 BC.
* [[Lothal]] of [[Indus Valley Civilization]] in [[India]] (3700 BCE).

