'''Peter Erler''' (born 10 April 1961 in [[Weißenfels]]) is a [[Germany|German]] [[historian]].   The focus of his professional research is on the history of German emigrants in the [[Soviet Union]], [[NKVD special camps in Germany 1945–49|Soviet internment camps]] in Germany, together with political developments more generally in the [[Soviet occupation zone]] (1945–1949) and the [[German Democratic Republic]] (1949–1990).<ref name=FUBPE>{{cite web|url=http://www.fu-berlin.de/sites/fsed/mitarbeiter/Mitarbeiter/erler/index.html|title= Peter Erler: Freie Universität Berlin - Mitglied der Redaktion der Zeitschrift des Forschungsverbundes|author=|date=19 March 2013|publisher= Freie Universität Berlin (Forschungsverbund SED-Staat)|accessdate=19 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=BiographischeDatenbankenPE>{{cite web|url=http://bundesstiftung-aufarbeitung.de/wer-war-wer-in-der-ddr-%2363%3B-1424.html?Aut=PeE|author2= |author1= |title=Angaben zum ... Peter Erler|publisher= Bundesstiftung zur Aufarbeitung der SED-Diktatur: Biographische Datenbanken |language= German| accessdate= 19 March 2015}}</ref>

Between 1980 and 1985 Peter Erler studied history and [[pedagogy]] at the [[Kuban State University]], [[Krasnodar]] in the [[Soviet Union]].   Since 1992 he has worked with both the {{illm|Forschungsverbund SED-Staat|de|Forschungsverbund SED-Staat}}, a department at the [[Free University of Berlin]], established in 1992 to perform research on "the external and internal pre-conditions for the forty year existence of a second German Dictatorship"<ref>"...„die äußeren und inneren Voraussetzungen der vierzigjährigen Existenz einer zweiten deutschen Diktatur"</ref><ref name=FUBFV>{{cite web|url=http://www.fu-berlin.de/sites/fsed/|title= Forschungsverbund SED-Staat an der Freien Universität |author=|date=19 March 2013|publisher= Freie Universität Berlin (Forschungsverbund SED-Staat)|accessdate=19 March 2015}}</ref> and the [[Berlin-Hohenschönhausen Memorial|Berlin-Hohenschönhausen Memorial Museum]].   He is also a member of the editorial staff of the newspaper of the Forschungsverbund.

